HEADWORD: Homoplasmy
<hw>Ho"mo*plas`my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ anything formed, fr. <?/ to form,
mold.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Resemblance between different
plants or animals, in external shape, in general habit, or in organs,
which is not due to descent from a common ancestor, but to similar
surrounding circumstances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homoplast</ent>⟦br⟧
